The paper discusses the use of logical reasoning and probabilistic belief revision in robotics, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of probabilistic belief revision also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also mentions the use of Answer Set Prolog (ASP), which is a declarative programming language and falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL).
